# Capture Protocol Requirements

Reject low-quality capture with clear retry instructions.

## Minimum Required Inputs

- 8-20 photos OR 10-60s video around room perimeter
- 50-80% overlap between adjacent frames/views
- At least 3 corners visible across set
- Floor-wall boundaries visible in multiple views
- At least one known-size reference in scene (marker/tape) OR depth/LiDAR metadata
- No heavy motion blur; no aggressive digital zoom

## Recommended Camera Behavior

- Keep camera at chest height for perimeter sweep
- Include oblique + straight-on views
- Capture each doorway/window from both sides when possible
- Keep constant exposure if possible
- Avoid occluding major surfaces with people

## Auto-Reject Conditions

- Missing floor visibility in most frames
- Severe blur or rolling-shutter distortion
- Insufficient overlap for reconstruction
- No scale reference and no depth source
- Single-view-only capture for complex room

## User-Facing Capture Instructions

Tell the user:
1. Record a slow perimeter video (10-30s), camera level, no zoom.
2. Include all corners, doorways, and window edges.
3. Put one known-size item in frame (A4 paper, printed marker, tape measure segment).
4. Take 6-12 still photos from mixed angles after video.
5. Avoid blur; good light; no people moving in room.
6. For best accuracy, include one manual measurement (door width or wall length).

## Perfect Mode (Error < 1-2%)

If accuracy target is strict:
- Require LiDAR-capable device OR
- Require at least 3 manual dimensions + marker-based scaling
- Reject reconstruction if uncertainty exceeds threshold
- Force recapture flow instead of guessing

## Reconstruction Pipeline

1) Quality gate — assess capture quality, reject if insufficient
2) Camera calibration / undistortion
3) SfM/SLAM + floor/wall plane extraction
4) Metric scale solve from references/depth/anchors
5) Semantic object detection + dimension priors
6) Constraint solve (hard physics first, soft priors second)
7) Final validation pass
8) Output layout OR recapture instructions
